definition: Cheney (name)/Richard B. "Dick" Cheney (1941-), US Republican politician, vice-president 2001-2008
definitely/absolutely (not)/(scoffing or dismissive interjection) Yeah, right./Tut!/to grind/close to/eager/to correspond to/see also 反切[fan3 qie4]
Buddhist nun/(often used in phonetic spellings)

sentences.english: What did Channy think of the defence work?
sentences.chinese: 切尼怎样看待防御工事？

sentences.english: Early vice presidents never played a Cheney-like role.
sentences.chinese: 早期的副总统们从来没有扮演过切尼的角色。

sentences.english: Perhaps he is afraid to speak on any topic at all without Dick Cheney pulling his strings.
sentences.chinese: 大概没有迪克切尼的幕后操纵他害怕谈论任何话题。

sentences.english: The problem may be Chenevert's promises for the future.
sentences.chinese: 问题可能出在切尼维特对未来的承诺上。

sentences.english: His energy policy was written by Mr Cheney with the help of a handful of cronies from the energy industry.
sentences.chinese: 他的能源措施由切尼先生和少数大能源集团起草。

sentences.english: Hillary and I had a last dance, and at about ten-thirty the Bushes and the Cheneys arrived.
sentences.chinese: 大约10点半，小布什夫妇和切尼夫妇到达了。

sentences.english: Punchinello walked up the narrow path and stepped into Eli's shop. His eyes grew big.
sentences.chinese: 庞切尼克走过一条窄路，进到以莱的店里。

sentences.english: Obama's speech was watched live on television by the audience at the Cheney event.
sentences.chinese: 观众们通过电视直播观看了奥巴马针对切尼的演说。

sentences.english: The vice president was a key architect of the U.S.-led invasion of Iraq.
sentences.chinese: 切尼是美国领导的攻打伊拉克战争的关键设计者。

sentences.english: Cheney was unapologetic about the harsh interrogation methods that he had approved, such as waterboarding.
sentences.chinese: 切尼对自己支持的诸如水刑的严刑逼供并未有悔意。

sentences.english: Cheney has signed a publishing deal to write his memoirs.
sentences.chinese: 切尼已经签了一份协议写他的传记。

sentences.english: Cheney also had an audience with Japanese Emperor Akihito and Empress Michiko later in the day.
sentences.chinese: 切尼还在当天晚上会见了日本天皇和皇后。

sentences.english: No accountability for Bush and Cheney's crimes, and those are slam-dunk felonies right there.
sentences.chinese: 布什和切尼不用为他们的罪行负责，那些深重的罪行。

sentences.english: That trend reached its apogee in Dick Cheney.
sentences.chinese: 这一趋势在切尼担任副总统时达到顶峰。

sentences.english: Exit interviews with Bush and Mr. Cheney have blanketed the media.
sentences.chinese: 布什与切尼先生的离别访问已经占领媒体。

sentences.english: Bashir needs to be in jail alongside Radko Mladic and Dick Cheney.
sentences.chinese: 巴舍尔和切尼他们应该关在监狱里。

definition: Gore (name)/Al Gore (1948-), US vice-president 1993-2001 under Bill Clinton, subsequently environmental campaigner and Nobel Peace laureate
Taiwan equivalent of 布什[Bu4 shi2]
